(496, 1, '2018-09-04 14:43:07', '2018-09-04 14:43:07', '[:zh]秘鲁美食被誉为是全世界最受欢迎的美食之一，其菜式的融合是长期以来文化交流的结果，集萃了西班牙的调味料、非洲、中国、日本和意大利风味。在秘鲁首都利马，你可以探索秘鲁最好的餐厅，品尝精致的传统秘鲁风味菜肴和其他融合菜肴。\r\n\r\n秘鲁将它的美食誉为全世界最好的，并连续六年在世界旅游奖（WTA）中被评为最佳美食目的地，这让秘鲁受到了全世界的关注，成为美食游客的特别关注，3家秘鲁风味的餐厅已经入选世界50佳。你的选择会让你的味蕾留下深刻的记忆！\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-492\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-1-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian cuisine\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n酸橘汁腌鱼是秘鲁的招牌美食，被认为是文化遗产，诞生于与日本料理的融合。这是一道用腌制的鱼或海鲜，浸入柑橘类水果（不同的胡椒与红辣椒）比如柠檬和酸橙而成的菜肴。酸橘汁腌鱼配煮熟的植物根比如甜土豆或木薯一起食用，有时配土豆、豆类、油炸车前草或是海草。\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-493\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-2-Copy-2-299x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian ceviche\" width=\"299\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nMestizaje突出了具有非洲传统的tacu-tacu，它的名字来源于盖丘亚语 takuy，意思是将一种东西与另一种混合，一种黑奴用来处理多余食物的烹饪方法，用来饱腹，度过艰难的岁月。 tacu tacu是一道用米饭混合着先前剩下的炖蔬菜（豆或小扁豆）的菜肴，还可以配鸡蛋、里脊肉和鸡肉。\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-494\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-3-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian tacu tacu\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nNovoandina美食是一种新的烹饪风格，发源于秘鲁，利用前西班牙美食去重新探索当地食材，同时与国际美食趋势结合。这类菜肴可以在秘鲁的豪华酒店里品尝到。在这些以Novoandina风格为特色的菜肴中，你可以品尝到油炸调味鱼、奎奴亚藜饭、丝兰和干土豆、蚝油豚鼠、鱿鱼和小牛肉还有很多其他美食。\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-495\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-4-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian cuisine\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n由于它的历史，秘鲁美食集中了不同的文化，使它成为了世界上独一无二以及无法抗拒的美食。\r\n\r\n<!--more-->[:en]Peruvian cuisine is considered one of the most favorite in the world, the fusion of its dishes is the result of cultural exchange through time, which highlights the seasoning of Spanish, African, Chinese, Japanese and Italian. In the capital, Lima, you will be able to explore the best restaurants in Peru and taste exquisite traditional Peruvian dishes and other fusion dishes.\r\n\r\nThe cuisine of this country has positioned itself as the best on the planet, Peru received for the sixth consecutive year the recognition as Best Culinary Destination of the World in the World Travel Awards (WTA) award that puts Peru before the eyes of the world and a privileged destination for gastronomic tourists, taking into account that 3 Peruvian restaurants are on the list of The 50 Best in the World. U destiny that will leave you memories full of flavors!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-492\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-1-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian cuisine\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe ceviche (tirados), Peruvian flag dish and considered cultural heritage, was born from the fusion with Japanese cuisine. It is a dish made with marinated fish and / or seafood meat, bathed in citrus fruits (varieties of pepper or chilli) such as lemon and lime. The ceviche is served with garnishes of boiled roots such as sweet potato or cassava and sometimes with potatoes, legumes, fried plantain or seaweed.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-493\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-2-Copy-2-299x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian ceviche\" width=\"299\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nMestizaje highlights the tacu-tacu that has an African heritage, its name comes from the Quechua takuy, which means combining one thing with the other, a cooking strategy used by the black slaves to take advantage of the excess food and calm their appetite when going through difficult times . The tacu tacu is a dish made of rice, but mixed with vegetable stew (beans or lentils) left over from the previous day and can be accompanied by egg, tenderloin or chicken.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-494\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-3-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian tacu tacu\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe Novoandina cuisine is a new culinary style that originated in Peru and that takes up the pre-Hispanic cuisine to rediscover indigenous ingredients and combine them with international gastronomic trends. This type of dishes can be tasted in luxurious hotels and restaurants in Peru. Among the dishes featured in the Novoandina cuisine you can find escabeche of fish with algarrobina, quinoa risotto, Ayacucho burst, yucca and dry potato carapulcra, guinea pig in oyster sauce, squid with veal and more delicacies.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-495\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-4-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"peruvian cuisine\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nResponding to its history, Peruvian cuisine concentrates diverse cultures, which makes it unique in the world and irresistible to the palate.[:]', '[:zh]秘鲁，美食爱好者的天堂。[:en]Peru, a destination for gastronomic tourists.[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e7%a7%98%e9%b2%81%ef%bc%8c%e7%be%8e%e9%a3%9f%e7%88%b1%e5%a5%bd%e8%80%85%e7%9a%84%e5%a4%a9%e5%a0%82%e3%80%82', '', '', '2018-09-04 14:43:07', '2018-09-04 14:43:07', '', 0, 'https://anditrip.com/?p=496', 0, 'post', '', 0),
