(605, 1, '2018-11-27 14:36:46', '2018-11-27 14:36:46', '[:zh]这座城市的海拔有足足2580米，并且其所拥有的保存最完好的南美的历史中心在1998年被评为世界文化遗产之一。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-609\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-4-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"391\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n最近几年，它的经济发展飞快，因此这个城市的旅游体验与基础建设得到了大幅度的提升。\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-606\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-4-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n它的高海拔使赋予了它稳定的山地气候，这让所有的游客都深深着迷。无处不在绿色植物以及善良朴实的人们，都让这个城市熠熠生辉。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-607\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-4-326x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"326\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n卡罗琳娜植物园以及盆栽博物馆只是这个城市游览点的一小部分，这难道不棒吗？\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-610\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-4-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n如果你去基多，你的两只脚随时随地都踩在地球的分界线上。您也可以参观这个30米高的纪念碑——它建造在一名法国探险家于1736年测量赤道时所在的位置上，这也是基多的一个非去不可的景点。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-608\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-5-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n<!--more-->[:en]This city located in the middle of the world is located at 2580 meters above sea level. It is known for having one of the best preserved historical centers of the continent, which made it, in 1998, declared Cultural Heritage of Humanity.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-609\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-4-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"391\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIn recent years, it has experienced great economic development, which has expanded the range of tourism services and experiences that can be found in Quito, Ecuador.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-606\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-4-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIts height makes it possessor of a permanent mountain climate, which pleases the locals and makes those who visit it fall in love. Green abounds in its spaces and the kindness of its people, is one of the characteristics of which they feel most proud.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-607\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-4-326x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"326\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nLa Carolina Park, the Botanical Garden along with the Bonsai Museum, are just some of the attractions it has to offer. Is that this Andean city is a set of virtues to discover.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-610\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-4-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIf you go to Quito, you can not stop standing with one foot in each of the halves of the world. Visit this monument of 30 meters high that is built on the site where a French explorer calculated that passes the line of the equator, in the year 1736. A mandatory destination of Ecuador.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-608\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-5-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n<!--more-->[:]', '[:zh]基多——世界中间的城市[:en]Quito, the city in the middle of the world[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e5%9f%ba%e5%a4%9a-%e4%b8%96%e7%95%8c%e4%b8%ad%e9%97%b4%e7%9a%84%e5%9f%8e%e5%b8%82', '', '', '2018-11-27 14:36:46', '2018-11-27 14:36:46', '', 0, 'https://anditrip.com/?p=605', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(543, 1, '2018-10-03 18:50:33', '2018-10-03 18:50:33', '[:zh]巴拿马的的宝藏——圣布拉斯群岛\r\n\r\n圣布拉斯群岛除了是巴拿马最主要的旅游地之外，还被认为是美洲大陆最美的地方之一。它由超过365个岛屿组成，还包括一些最美的沙滩。在岛上，你可以舒展身心，住在美丽的自然野生风景中，使你感觉到无与伦比的放松。你将在巴拿马收获巴拿马充满异域风情以及天堂般的愉悦体验！\r\n\r\n在圣布拉斯群岛，你可以享受两处独一无二的景点，加勒比海岛的美以及拜访古纳斯印第安人的村庄。去探索学习他们的迷人文化以及生活方式。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-528\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-1-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n365个小岛组成了圣布拉斯群岛，但只有其中80个有人居住。土著古纳人是拥有这片土地的种族，并且他们以善良以及对艺术的敏感性为特点，尤其是装饰艺术。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-529\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-2-Copy-292x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"292\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n他们的房屋由稻草屋顶和从岛上砍下的木头建成，并且用他们手工制作的小船捕鱼以及种植热带植物维持生计。龙虾、椰子和香蕉是这个少数民族食谱上最基本的食品。古纳的妇女以她们五彩缤纷的裙子以及美丽的手工衬衫著称，每一款设计都是独一无二、原汁原味的， 并且反映了自然和古纳人的精神生活。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-530\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-3-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"329\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n在这个群岛上，你可以穿越千年文化，品味它的舞蹈、音乐、语言、食物以及生活方式。这里也是加勒比人的天堂，你可以体验浮潜、深潜、皮划艇或凝视沙滩、如水晶般透明的海水和棕榈树。这是一个令人不可思议的天堂，值得用你的双眼去发现。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-531\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-4-Copy-220x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"220\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n让你远离纷繁世界的理想之地！\r\n\r\n火山：大自然的铁匠\r\n\r\n在巴拿马有超过13座休眠火山群，巴鲁火山、安东山谷、拉耶瓜达火山是全国最著名的三座，由于它们可以对游客全面开放。毫无疑问，天然温泉的天堂，火山喷发的熔岩形成的山脉、泻湖和在火山口形成的水之眼已经熄灭。\r\n\r\n安东山谷位于一座古老的休眠火山上，气候凉爽，是自然爱好者的理想之地。这里有小径、山脉和无数花草树木、哺乳动物、爬行动物和超过350种鸟类。在这里你可以享受spa和医疗，基于这里的温泉、泥浆和火山石。一个非常舒适、独特和自然的体验！\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-532\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-5-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n巴鲁火山国家公园是最主要的旅游景点之一，你可以自己攀爬火山，亲眼见证太平洋和加勒比海之间美丽的日出。这里栖息的250多种鸟类比如啄木鸟、金灿灿的绿咬鹃和黑胸峰鸟。在公园内还栖息着巨大的猫科动物比如豹子和美洲狮，还有其他哺乳动物比如豪猪。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-533\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-6-Copy-352x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"352\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n拉耶瓜达森林保护区是一个露营的绝佳场所，这是一个有着茂盛绿松的小小天堂，泻湖由古老的火山口形成，还有凉爽的气候，让你身心放松。在旅程中你可以\r\n看到森林种植园、宽阔又如水晶般清澈的河流以及群山。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-534\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-7-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n达连国家公园——茂密的森林、丰富的传统\r\n\r\n这片热带雨林位于巴拿马东部，哥伦比亚边界处，它的生物多样性和自然空间被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗产。在这片绿色的天堂里你可以看到鸟儿、通航的河流以及土著部落，这是一个充满冒险的地方，用它美和神秘给你留下难以忘怀的记忆，是巴拿马之旅不容错过的一站！\r\n\r\n达连公园被认为是亚马逊丛林的发源地，也是各种植物和动物的家园，这也是为什么这里的生态红线以及生物多样性有超过40种当地的兰花物种和约450种鸟类。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-535\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-8-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n达连公园最好的景点在Santa Cruz de Cana公园和Pirre站。第一块区域非常令人不可思议，你可以看到野生动物，也是最好的观鸟点之一，比如不同颜色的金刚鹦鹉、鹰、蜂鸟和巨嘴鸟，你还可以看到吼猴、貘和蜘蛛。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-536\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-9-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nPierre站拥有茂盛的森林和丰富的野生动物和种类繁多的鸟类，你可以看到啄木鸟等。你还可以在哺乳动物中找到蛛猴、白脸和树懒等。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-537\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-10-Copy-304x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"304\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n在达连公园，有3个土著部落，Wounaan、Emberá是Chocó的土著居民，还有公园北部Tacarcuna山附近的Kunas。这些少数民族用他们的传统将你带回前哥伦比亚时期，你将情不自禁的享受它的舞蹈和风俗，不仅仅做一个其日常生活的见证者。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-538\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-11-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n去往达连公园的美妙风景将是一个冒险与经历结合的体验！\r\n\r\n<!--more-->[:en]The treasure of Panama, the San Blas archipelago\r\n\r\nSan Blas is an archipelago considered one of the most beautiful places of the American continent, besides being the main tourist destination of the country. It is composed of more than 365 islands comprising some of the most beautiful beaches. On this island you can lose yourself and live in the beauty of its natural landscapes and wildlife that will make you reach a state of unparalleled relaxation. A pleasant experience in a paradisiacal and exotic place in Panama!\r\n\r\nIn the San Blas archipelago you can enjoy two unique attractions, the beauty of its Caribbean islands and the opportunity to visit the hamlets of the Gunas Indians, to discover and learn about their fascinating culture and way of life.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-528\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-1-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nOf the 365 small islands that make up the archipelago, only 80 are inhabited. The indigenous Guna people are the ethnic group that owns this territory and they are a people that is characterized by their kindness and their sensitivity to art, especially decorative art.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-529\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-2-Copy-292x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"292\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nTheir houses are made with straw roofs and cut wood from the island. They subsist on fishing in their handmade boats and the cultivation of tropical plants. Lobster, coconut and bananas are basic provisions in the diet of this ethnic group. The Kuna women stand out with their colorful dresses and beautiful hand-made blouses, each of the designs is unique, original and reflects the nature and spiritual life of the Gunas.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-530\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-3-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"329\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIn this archipelago you can travel in the time experienced a thousand-year-old culture, its dances, its music, its language, its food and the way of life, but it is also a paradise of the Caribbean where you can practice snorkeling, diving, kayaking and contemplating white sands , crystal clear waters and palm trees, an almost indescribable paradise that is worth seeing with your own eyes.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-531\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-4-Copy-220x220.jpg\" alt=\"Panama\" width=\"220\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe perfect place to disconnect from the world!\r\n\r\nThe volcanoes; smiths of beautiful nature\r\n\r\nIn Panama there are more than 13 inactive volcanic complexes and El Volcán Barú, El Valle de Antón and La Yeguada are the best known in the country, since they allow total access to tourists and visitors. Without a doubt, paradisiacal territories with natural thermal waters, mountains raised by lava eruptions, lagoons and eyes of water formed in volcanic craters already extinguished.\r\n\r\nThe valley of Antón is built on an old inactive volcano, has a cool climate and is the ideal place for nature lovers. It has trails, mountains and countless species of flowers, trees, mammals, reptiles and more than 350 types of birds of different species. Here you can enjoy spa services and medicinal treatments based on hot springs, mud and volcanic stones. A very comforting, unique and other natural experience!\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-532\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-5-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe Barú Volcano National Park has become one of the main tourist attractions, because you can climb the Volcano and witness beautiful sunrises between the Pacific Ocean and the Caribbean Sea. In it live 250 species of birds such as the woodpecker, the resplendent quetzal, the black-chested hummingbird among others. Inside the park live very large cats such as leopards and pumas, as well as other mammals such as porcupines\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-533\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-6-Copy-352x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"352\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nLa Yeguada Forest Reserve is ideal for camping, a small paradise where its beautiful landscapes loaded with green pines, its lagoon that is an old crater and the cool climate, allows you to live a very relaxing experience. In your journey you will find forest plantations, large and crystal clear rivers, as well as mountains.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-534\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-7-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nDarién National Park, lush forests and traditions\r\n\r\nThis tropical forest is located east of Panama on the border with the Republic of Colombia, its biological diversity and natural space were recognized as a World Heritage Site by Unesco. Within this green paradise you can see birds, navigable rivers and indigenous communities, a place full of adventures and unforgettable experiences with a mixture of beauty and mystery that you should not miss during your trip to Panama\r\n\r\nDarien Park is considered the starting point of the Amazon rainforest and is home to a variety of plant and animal species, which is why its ecological wealth and biodiversity are represented in more than 40 endemic species of orchids and about 450 birds.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-535\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-8-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe best places to visit in Darién are the Santa Cruz de Cana park and the Pirre station. The first one is an incredible area where you can see the wildlife and is one of the best places for bird watching, such as macaws of different shades, eagles, hummingbirds and toucans, you can also see howler monkeys, tapirs and spiders.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-536\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-9-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe Pierre Station, also has lush forests and abundant wildlife, the largest number of species of birds that you can see here are the tangars, the frenzied nun and woodpeckers. Among the mammals you will find the spider monkey, aulladror and the white face and the sloths.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-537\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-10-Copy-304x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"304\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIn Darién, there are 3 indigenous groups, the Wounaan, the Emberá, the traditional inhabitants of the Chocó and the Kunas north of the park near the Tacarcuna hill, these ethnies will transport you with their traditions to the pre-Columbian era, so you can not stop enjoying his dances and customs, besides being a witness of his daily life.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-538\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Imagen-11-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"panama\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nGoing into the landscapes of Parque Darién is combining adventure and experience!\r\n\r\n<!--more-->[:]', '[:zh]巴拿马的绿色角落[:en]The green corners of Panama[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e5%b7%b4%e6%8b%bf%e9%a9%ac%e7%9a%84%e7%bb%bf%e8%89%b2%e8%a7%92%e8%90%bd', '', '', '2018-10-03 18:50:33', '2018-10-03 18:50:33', '', 0, 'https://anditrip.com/?p=543', 0, 'post', '', 0),
