(597, 1, '2018-11-05 15:27:32', '2018-11-05 15:27:32', '[:zh]<!--more-->\r\n\r\n有些美食搭配红酒方能突显其美味，旅途也是如此。\r\n加入我们，了解南美生产红酒的地方，享受随着时间推移而更显醇厚的美酒。\r\n\r\n智利，埃尔基谷。皮斯科，天文与诗歌。\r\n智利是这个地区主要的葡萄酒生产地之一，有着各种各样的山谷，为葡萄酒的生产形成了得天独厚的条件。位于距离圣地亚哥500km处，也是智利的首都，是智利红酒区的北部边界。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-596\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-2-326x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"326\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n这里的土肥沃，有着丰富的营养，储水能力强，这也是为什么能生产出成熟而又甜的葡萄，这就是皮斯科的原料地，这是一种典型的智利饮料。同时，在山谷中还培养着赤霞珠、梅鹿辄、卡梅尼埃和霞多丽的品种，所以，毫无疑问，找到适合你用餐的好酒将不会是问题。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-593\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n这个部分的智利是南半球最纯净的天空之一，这也就是为什么各种国际组织在这里设立天文观测站的原因。在夜晚，不经意间就可以瞥见星星，所以来到这里或是在山谷某个角落露营将会是独一无二的经历，只有南美大陆可以带给你。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-2-452x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"452\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n另一面，在山谷里，是比库尼亚城，埃尔基谷的首府，也是智利著名诗人Gabriela Mistral出生和居住的地方。在这座城市的众多景点中最吸引人的是以他名字命名的博物馆，还有普克拉罗水库，建于1996年8月，为你带来理想的风帆冲浪、风筝冲浪和风筝冲浪的气候条件。毫无疑问，埃尔基谷拥有的多样性的景点，使它成为一个你不会想要停止访问的目的地。\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-595\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-2-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n伊卡，秘鲁的历史和红酒。\r\n伊卡是秘鲁皮斯科酒的发源地，是秘鲁一种典型的饮料。\r\n伊卡是秘鲁沿海沙漠和安第斯山脉的一部分，是全国农业出口潜力最大的中心之一，因此赋予了它重要的社会经济地位。然而事实上，这里是葡萄酒庄园最早起源的地方，由西班牙人带来，一段时间后，传播到智利和阿根廷。在这里你可以游览不同的庄园和葡萄酒园，在这里你可以目睹皮斯科酒和这个地区红酒从生产过程到产品的过程。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-587\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-5-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"329\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n秘鲁这个区域另一个吸引人的地方是帕拉卡斯国家自然保护区，一个海洋和沙漠被保护的部分，为了保护这里当地不同的物种和迁徙的鸟儿，例如鹈鹕、企鹅、火烈鸟，还有其他哺乳动物。这里的岛屿、沙漠、悬崖和沙滩占地有335公顷，由于其令人印象深刻的自然美景，每年吸引着当地和海外的游客前来。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-588\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-6-Copy-383x220.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"383\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n谈及秘鲁，不只有印加文化，还有纳斯卡文化，你可以在安东尼奥博物馆和玛利亚瑞奇博物馆里了解到更多，这里曾经是一个德国女人的家，她曾致力于研究纳斯卡曲线，并被联合国教科文组织命名为人类世界文化遗产。在安东尼奥博物馆，你可以看到纳斯卡文化不同时期的考古样本，例如织物等。另外，你还可以欣赏Bisambra隧道，其展示了纳斯卡文化这个时期伟大的水力工程。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-589\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-7-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n门多萨，阿根廷最重要的红酒中心\r\n以国际红酒之都而闻名，在门多萨，你可以欣赏自然、文化活动和最好的美食。它的自然特征为生产不同类型的优质葡萄酒提供了理想的条件，其中马尔贝克葡萄酒最为突出，其酒香在其他地区很难找到。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-590\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-8-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n全年被树木与适宜的气候所包围，这座阿根廷城市的山脉是其主角，毫无疑问是你想前往的地方。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-591\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-9-Copy-455x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"455\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n在市区你可以找到不同的博物馆和艺术画廊，其中有葡萄酒博物馆，Cuyano 的过往博物馆以及基础地区博物馆，包含了一个藏有门多萨地房间与门多萨的卡比尔多考古遗迹。参观他们将让你了解和了解门多萨的文化，以及品尝该地区生产的葡萄酒的精美样品。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-592\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-10-Copy-367x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"367\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n这里还有令人满意的户外活动。在门多萨，你可以享受温泉水，辅以酒店和水疗设施。同时，在门多萨河，几乎全年都可以进行漂流，如果我们稍微再远离城市一点，就可以到达firewoods，一个垂直不均匀度为1200米的滑雪中心，有住宿和美食一流棒。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-586\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-11-Copy-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"391\" height=\"220\" />[:en]<!--more-->\r\n\r\nSome meals are enjoyed more with a bit of wine, with travel the same thing happens.\r\n\r\nAn exquisite trip. Wine tasting in South America.\r\n\r\nSome meals are enjoyed more with a bit of wine, with travel the same thing happens.\r\n\r\nJoin us to know the South American destinations where it is produced and enjoy this delicious drink that improves over time.\r\n\r\nValley of Elqui, in Chile. Pisco, astronomy and poetry.\r\nWith a variety of valleys with the ideal conditions for the formation of vineyards, Chile is one of the main wine producers in the region. Located about 500km from Santiago, the capital of the country, the Elqui Valley forms the northern border of Chile\'s wine regions.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-596\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-2-326x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"326\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIts soil is dense, rich in nutrients and capable of storing water, which is why sweet and ripe grapes are produced, from which Pisco is obtained, a typical Chilean drink. Also, in this valley are cultivated strains of Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Carménère and Chardonnay, so undoubtedly, find good wine to accompany your meals, will not be a problem.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-593\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-2-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThis part of Chile has one of the clearest skies in the southern hemisphere, which is why various international organizations have installed astronomical observatories in the area. At night, the stars can be glimpsed easily, so to visit them or camp in one of the corners of the valley, will be a unique experience that only this southern region of the American continent can offer you.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-2-452x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"452\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, valley inside, is the city of Vicuña, capital of the Elqui Valley and place where Gabriela Mistral, the famous Chilean poestisa, was born and lived. Among the attractions of this city are the museum that bears his name, as well as the Puclaro Reservoir, which, since its construction in August 1996, offers all year round the ideal climatic conditions for windsurfing, kite surfing and kiteboarding. Definitely, the diversity of attractions that Valle de Elqui has, make it a destination that you will not want to stop visiting.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-595\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-2-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIca, history and wines in Peru.\r\nIca is the place of origin of the Peruvian Pisco, typical drink of the country.\r\n\r\nPart of the coastal desert of Peru and part of the Andes mountain range, Ica is one of the centers with the greatest agro-export potential in the country, which has given it great socioeconomic importance. And in fact, it was to this place where the vineyards arrived for the first time, brought by the Spaniards, for some time later to take them to Chile and Argentina. Here you can visit different haciendas and vineyards, where you can witness the different processes that lead to the production of pisco and the wines of this region.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-587\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-5-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"329\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nAnother attraction of this region of Peru is the Paracas National Reserve, a protected portion of sea and desert, in order to preserve different species of resident and migratory birds, such as pelicans, penguins, flamingos, among other marine species. There are 335 hectares of islands, deserts, cliffs and beaches, which thanks to its impressive natural beauty, attracts local and foreign tourists annually.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-588\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-6-Copy-383x220.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"383\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nTalking about Peru is not only about the Inca culture, but also about the Nazca culture, and you can learn more about it in the Antonini Museum and the María Reiche Museum, which used to be the home of this German woman who dedicated herself to study the Nazca lines, declared cultural heritage of humanity by UNESCO. In the Antonini Museum you will find archaeological samples from different stages of the Nazca culture, such as textiles and museums. In addition, it is possible to appreciate the Bisambra channel, which shows the magnificent hydraulic engineering work of this culture.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-589\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-7-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nMendoza, the most important wine center in Argentina.\r\n\r\nKnown as the international capital of wine, in Mendoza you can enjoy nature, cultural activities and the best cuisine in one place. Its natural characteristics propitiate the ideal conditions for the production of different types of exquisite wines, among which the Malbec stands out, with a bouquet difficult to find in other regions.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-590\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-8-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nSurrounded by trees and with a pleasant climate throughout the year, this Argentine city where the mountain range is the protagonist, is one of those destinations to which you will undoubtedly want to return.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-591\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-9-Copy-455x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"455\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIn its urban area you can find different museums and art galleries, among which are the Wine Museum, the Museum of the Cuyano Past and the Museum of the Foundational Area, which contains an underground chamber with the archaeological remains of the Cabildo of Mendoza. Visiting them will allow you to get to know and get into the culture of Mendoza, as well as taste exquisite samples of the wines produced in the region.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-592\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-10-Copy-367x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"367\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIts offer of outdoor activities leaves nothing to be desired. In Mendoza you can enjoy warm thermal waters complemented by the attention and amenities of hotels and spas. Also, in the Mendoza River it is possible to do rafting during almost all the year, and if we move away a little of the city, we can arrive at the firewoods, a ski center with a vertical unevenness of 1200 meters, that has lodging and gastronomy first level.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-586\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-11-Copy-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"391\" height=\"220\" />[:]', '[:zh]精致之旅。南美红酒品尝。[:en]An exquisite trip. Wine tasting in South America.[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '585-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-05 15:27:32', '2018-11-05 15:27:32', '', 585, 'https://anditrip.com/585-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(598, 1, '2018-11-05 16:10:47', '2018-11-05 16:10:47', '[:zh]巴西与阿根廷所共有的世界奇观\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n伊瓜苏大瀑布的源头为从巴西的巴拉那州流出的伊瓜苏河。当然您也可以在距离阿根廷的米西奥内斯省的伊瓜苏港20公里外的伊瓜苏国家公园中找到一些与之同名的瀑布。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-602\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-3-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n它在1984年被宣布为世界文化遗产，并且在2011年被提名为一个由两个美丽国家所共有的七大自然奇观之一。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-599\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n您无法想象这样的一个奇观背后有多么巨大的能量——高达80米的水位差带来的冲击在这茂密的森林中基本是不可比拟的。在这里，您可以在人行道与观景台享受到这种大自然带给您无与伦比的视觉冲击。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-600\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-3-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n不止如此，您还可以做更多。您可以选择参与一个由当地导游所带领的穿越丛林的行程并借此来感受这里的动植物群，您也可以分别到达伊瓜苏瀑布在阿根廷与巴西的两个部分——在这两个国家，您都可以能提供舒适旅行服务的城市来帮助您更好的体验这一奇观。\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-601\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />[:en]Brazil and Argentina share a wonder.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nFormed by the Iguazú River that originates in the state of Paraná, Brazil, the falls of the same name are found within the Iguazú National Park, some 20 kilometers from the city of Puerto Iguazú, north of the province of Misiones, Argentina.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-602\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-3-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nDeclared natural heritage of humanity in 1984, in 2011 they were nominated for an international contest as one of the 7 Natural Wonders of the World, shared by two beautiful countries.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-599\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nThe energy they transmit is incredible. It treats falls of water of up to 80 meters, in the middle of a dense forest to which it is possible to accede by different means. In the place, there are walkways and viewpoints from which it is possible to contemplate its majesty and enjoy this spectacle of nature.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-600\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-3-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nHowever, you can be more than a spectator. It is possible to take guided tours through the adjacent jungle and admire the great diversity of flora and fauna present in the place. You can get to the Iguazú Falls on the Argentine side or on the Brazilian side, and the cities of both countries have hotels and tourist services so you can get to know this wonder, with all the amenities you want.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-601\" src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"220\" />[:]', '[:zh]伊瓜苏大瀑布[:en]Iguazu falls[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e4%bc%8a%e7%93%9c%e8%8b%8f%e5%a4%a7%e7%80%91%e5%b8%83', '', '', '2018-11-05 16:10:47', '2018-11-05 16:10:47', '', 0, 'https://anditrip.com/?p=598', 0, 'post', '', 0),
